# ModelBound skill authoring

When editing skill files (`.modelbound/`, `.kiro/skills/`, `.cursor/rules/`, `.claude/`, `.agents/skills/**/SKILL.md`, or legacy `skills/` paths):

1. **Preserve YAML frontmatter.** Never silently drop, rename, or blank the `name`, `description`, `version`, `model`, or `tags` keys.
2. **Token-conscious edits.** Prefer surgical edits over full rewrites. If a rewrite is necessary, propose running `/mb-optimize` afterward.
3. **Trust before pipeline.** After substantive edits, suggest `/mb-findings <file>` then `/mb-pipeline <file> --stage test_optimize`.
4. **Never invent versions or UUIDs.** Use file paths or slugs with `/mb-versions <file>` — the CLI resolves UUIDs via sync.
5. **Restore is non-destructive.** Restoring an old version creates a new version on top of history; reassure the user nothing is lost.

When the user pastes a skill file into chat without a path, ask whether they want a local diff (`/mb-optimize ./path`) or a cloud-tracked one (`/mb-sync ./path` then `/mb-findings ./path`).
